column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2
#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Chiara
#Text=:
#Text=When I go into a competition , I always go to win , but I was nervous like everyone else ...
#Text=I think [ when ] you win a festival , [ you win ] for what you present , not for what your history is .
#Text=( (
#Text=Mike Halterman
#Text=) )
#Text=Growing up , did you always want to become a singer ?
#Text=Who were your musical influences , and what genres do you think are your favorite ?
#Text=Do you think these preferences have molded you into the singer you are today ?
#Text=Chiara
#Text=: Definitely .
#Text=My mum always says I used to sing and dance for them all the time since I was a baby , and I 've always loved ballads .
#Text=In fact , my favourite singer has always been Whitney Houston .
#Text=( (
#Text=Mike Halterman
#Text=) )
#Text=How did you come to the decision to enter the Eurovision pre-selection for Malta back in 1998 ?
#Text=What kinds of feelings did you experience during the path you took to eventual victory in the national final ?
#Text=Chiara
#Text=: 1998 was my first time in the festival .
#Text=I was very young and I felt I could never win it .
#Text=I wanted just to try and be there with the big names of those times .
#Text=It was very scary and overwhelming , [ and ] then I won .
#Text=( (
#Text=Mike Halterman
#Text=) )
#Text=Did you feel overwhelmed performing in front of an international audience in Birmingham ?
#Text=What kind of personal feelings and emotions made you relate to the song you sang , " The One That I Love " ?

#Text=There were remarks afterwards that your performance was great , but your dress had similarities to Barbara Dex 's from five years before ( and she has become well-known for her " fashion do n't " ) .
#Text=Looking back on it , what did you think of that dress ?
#Text=Chiara
#Text=: Well ... looking back I remember that I was completely overwhelmed [ singing ] in front of so many people .
#Text=I was very scared but managed to do well .
#Text=As for the dress , they were different times [ back then ] and it was beyond my control .
#Text=( (
#Text=Mike Halterman
#Text=) )
#Text=You came very close to winning the Contest for Malta back in 1998 .
#Text=When you did n't , how did it make you feel ?
#Text=Did you feel " robbed " ?

#Text=As an addenda , some Wikipedians I 've talked to have hypothesized that tabloid hype before the event helped Dana International win ; in other words , she would not have won had she not been a transsexual .
#Text=Do you feel that 's true , and did you like her song ?
#Text=Chiara
#Text=:
#Text=I know a lot of Maltese who voted for Dana because they liked the song and for no other reason .
#Text=The song was good and we still hear it today .
#Text=Obviously when you are so close to winning something and you do n't , yes , you feel a bit robbed , but [ then there 's ] the moment [ when ] you realise you did well and you are happy .
